parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause a loss of steering and braking, increasing the risk of accidents.
Oil pressure switch failure can cause the engine to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Engine cooling system failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine failure, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.

The peeling and delamination of the paint can lead to rust and corrosion, which can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, potentially causing safety issues. Additionally, the peeling paint can create a hazard for other drivers on the road if it detaches while driving.
symptoms: Large sections of paint peeling off
and doors; paint chipping and flaking off; delamination of paint; rust and corrosion exposure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Backup Camera and Radio System)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can lead to a loss of critical safety features, such as the backup camera, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Backup camera and radio system failure; loss of electrical power to certain systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine can cause a loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Engine stalling; transmission failure; loss of power and acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door handle can cause difficulties in entering and exiting the vehicle, potentially leading to safety issues in emergency situations.
symptoms: Door handle breakage; difficulty opening and closing doors.
